28
00:02:56,598 --> 00:02:58,828
Look, look, look at this!

29
00:02:59,534 --> 00:03:00,493
Here.

30
00:03:01,269 --> 00:03:03,669
"Trash" is the name of our dog.

31
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:10,173
He was looking forward to surprising you with his own art exhibition.

32
00:03:11,446 --> 00:03:15,244
Then, why didn't he send that postcard?

33
00:03:16,485 --> 00:03:19,352
His exhibition was cancelled.

34
00:03:20,656 --> 00:03:22,180
Cancelled?

35
00:03:23,225 --> 00:03:27,386
It was Yuuji's mother who brought the idea of an art exhibition.

36
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:29,961
His mother?

37
00:03:30,732 --> 00:03:33,064
He met his mother?

38
00:03:34,770 --> 00:03:39,563
His mother said she was going out with a famous art dealer for some art gallery.

39
00:03:39,608 --> 00:03:41,405
He liked Yuuji's drawings,

40
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:44,343
so they were going to open an art exhibition and sell his drawings.

41
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:47,810
Yes, I deposited the money this morning.

42
00:03:48,016 --> 00:03:49,313
Thank you.

43
00:03:49,551 --> 00:03:50,779
Oh, and...

44
00:03:51,019 --> 00:03:53,613
please take a good care of my mother.

45
00:04:02,798 --> 00:04:04,891
He became ecstatic,

46
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:08,333
and even borrowed money to make it happen.

47
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:09,700
But...

48
00:04:11,907 --> 00:04:14,432
[ This number is no longer being used. ]

49
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:17,804
[ Please call again with the right number. ]

50
00:04:22,017 --> 00:04:24,918
The whole deal was a lie.

51
00:04:25,454 --> 00:04:27,684
They defrauded his money.

52
00:04:29,324 --> 00:04:30,484
They betrayed you!

53
00:04:30,792 --> 00:04:32,384
It's a fraud!

54
00:04:33,428 --> 00:04:34,918
Let's report to the police!

55
00:04:35,030 --> 00:04:37,726
It doesn't matter for me.

56
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:41,291
As long as that money helps my mom and her boyfriend...

57
00:04:41,803 --> 00:04:43,168
It's fine by me.

58
00:04:50,712 --> 00:04:53,647
This is the sketchbook he always carried around.

59
00:05:05,894 --> 00:05:09,796
He always drew that picture when he hit a dead end.

60
00:05:17,606 --> 00:05:22,878
"I have at least two true friends who believed I can become an artist,"

61
00:05:22,878 --> 00:05:24,869
he said.

62
00:05:31,185 --> 00:05:32,683
Yuuji...

63
00:06:07,722 --> 00:06:09,485
Hey, let's go.

64
00:06:16,031 --> 00:06:18,659
Back then...

65
00:06:20,302 --> 00:06:22,993
...the three of us were here all the time.

66
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:27,899
But...

67
00:06:28,643 --> 00:06:32,504
sometimes, I think...

68
00:06:34,850 --> 00:06:41,242
Maybe everything happened in this town was a dream.

69
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:50,957
It's not a dream.

70
00:06:52,701 --> 00:06:58,302
Because Yuuji waited for us in this very town.

71
00:07:01,676 --> 00:07:02,973
You're moving?

72
00:07:04,179 --> 00:07:07,410
My mom is being transferred to a hospital far away.

73
00:07:07,515 --> 00:07:09,214
You'll be going to another school?

74
00:07:10,785 --> 00:07:11,781
Yes.

75
00:07:21,963 --> 00:07:25,364
But I'm sure we'll meet again.

76
00:07:27,502 --> 00:07:30,364
The three of us will always be together.

77
