When I become the owner of an aqua plants shop,

277
00:37:46,219 --> 00:37:48,414
I'll name it "Trash".

278
00:37:49,589 --> 00:37:52,683
You're the mascot girl for Trash.

279
00:38:42,542 --> 00:38:45,272
Hey, Karin. Do you remember?

280
00:38:45,378 --> 00:38:47,175
The seeds of water lily.

281
00:38:49,015 --> 00:38:53,281
It may take more than 50 years to sprout up.

282
00:38:53,987 --> 00:38:57,787
But it will definitely sprout one day.

283
00:39:00,226 --> 00:39:02,087
It will wake up.

284
00:39:21,281 --> 00:39:25,581
[ I don't care if you stay asleep. ]

285
00:39:26,853 --> 00:39:30,983
[ I'll keep talking to you. ]

286
00:39:44,804 --> 00:39:46,863
How long will you be staying in Paris?

287
00:39:47,373 --> 00:39:50,365
I want to train myself until I'm satisfied.

288
00:39:51,110 --> 00:39:52,099
I see.

289
00:39:57,217 --> 00:39:58,912
Chocolate danish.

290
00:39:59,185 --> 00:40:02,018
My last and greatest masterpiece.

291
00:40:03,389 --> 00:40:04,647
Thank you.

292
00:40:07,227 --> 00:40:08,421
Satoshi.

293
00:40:10,964 --> 00:40:15,694
Waiting is not easy, is it?

294
00:40:18,905 --> 00:40:20,269
But...

295
00:40:20,540 --> 00:40:26,438
I think it's wonderful that you're accepting your own feelings now.

296
00:40:29,315 --> 00:40:30,577
Misaki...

297
00:40:32,886 --> 00:40:34,410
I'll write you.

298
00:40:37,090 --> 00:40:38,482
Good luck.

299
00:40:39,192 --> 00:40:41,319
You too.

300
00:40:54,407 --> 00:40:55,772
Hey, Karin.

301
00:40:56,876 --> 00:40:59,868
Yuuji and Momoka has a baby now.

302
00:41:00,546 --> 00:41:03,208
I'm sure it's a cute baby.

303
00:41:06,700 --> 00:41:09,027
( And so, Nello and Patrasche woke up,
and lived happily ever after. )

304
00:41:09,188 --> 00:41:11,315
Thank you so much for everything.

305
00:41:18,898 --> 00:41:22,231
[ Natsume finally became a certified accountant. ]

306
00:41:23,736 --> 00:41:25,101
[ I'm stumped! ]

307
00:41:25,638 --> 00:41:29,703
[ Now I have to place orders and do the packaging all by myself. ]

308
00:41:30,009 --> 00:41:31,970
[ Delivery too. ]

309
00:41:34,347 --> 00:41:35,579
Hey,

310
00:41:36,449 --> 00:41:37,677
Karin.

311
00:41:50,063 --> 00:41:53,328
His eyes look exactly like Yuuji's!

312
00:41:54,300 --> 00:41:56,063
Her name is Haruka.

313
00:41:56,202 --> 00:41:59,365
Oh, I see.

314
00:42:02,942 --> 00:42:05,672
I wish Karin can see her.

315
00:42:21,861 --> 00:42:23,522
[ Hey, Karin. ]

316
00:42:25,164 --> 00:42:28,998
[ I can wait for you, right? ]

317
00:42:41,781 --> 00:42:46,077
[ You'll wake up again someday, right? ]

318
00:42:48,654 --> 00:42:50,722
[ I can believe in you, right? ]

319
00:42:53,259 --> 00:42:54,351
[ Hey, ]

320
00:42:56,162 --> 00:42:58,220
[ Karin? ]

321
00:43:19,986 --> 00:43:21,681
Thank you very much.

322
00:43:40,807 --> 00:43:43,833
Can you switch these two?

323
00:43:44,310 --> 00:43:45,868
Thank you.

324
00:43:47,180 --> 00:43:48,545
Hey, Satoshi.

325
00:43:48,848 --> 00:43:49,837
Congratulations.

326
00:43:49,949 --> 00:43:50,847
Thank you.

327
00:43:51,417 --> 00:43:53,783
My dad wanted to come too, but...

328
00:43:54,487 --> 00:43:56,216
He's still not feeling well?

329
00:43:56,322 --> 00:43:57,386
Yes.

330
00:44:00,827 --> 00:44:02,494
At last.

331
00:44:03,830 --> 00:44:06,157
It took 5 years though.

332
00:44:09,335 --> 00:44:12,067
A lot of things happened on the way,

333
00:44:13,873 --> 00:44:16,637
but I think they were all meaningful.

334
00:44:31,324 --> 00:44:33,315
I drew it for Karin.

335
00:44:36,829 --> 00:44:39,791
By the time I realized how I felt about her,

336
00:44:40,399 --> 00:44:43,090
she was already in love with you.

337
00:44:51,744 --> 00:44:53,272
I think maybe...

338
00:44:54,180 --> 00:44:57,381
Karin was hoping you would wait for her.

339
00:45:55,541 --> 00:45:58,237
I was dreaming.

340
00:46:02,048 --> 00:46:06,917
A dream of when you were born.

341
00:46:12,191 --> 00:46:17,284
It was a difficult delivery.

342
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:23,930
Your mom and I,

343
00:46:25,504 --> 00:46:28,337
we were in tears from happiness.

344
00:46:34,213 --> 00:46:38,313
It's was the first time in my life...

345
00:46:42,555 --> 00:46:45,255
...I felt so warm inside.

346
00:46:51,197 --> 00:46:52,794
I'm sorry.

347
00:46:55,234 --> 00:46:57,001
What is it?

348
00:47:01,574 --> 00:47:03,532
I should've...

349
00:47:05,945 --> 00:47:08,135
...started a family,

350
00:47:09,315 --> 00:47:12,716
so you wouldn't worry about me.

351
00:47:30,336 --> 00:47:35,803
You should live the way you want to.

352
00:47:39,745 --> 00:47:44,507
That's how I intended to raise you.

353
00:48:16,816 --> 00:48:19,015
You two,

354
00:48:20,653 --> 00:48:24,345
...are connected through a powerful force.

355
00:48:26,792 --> 00:48:32,187
Your mother and I...

356
00:48:34,266 --> 00:48:37,962
...are connected to you with the same force.

357
00:48:53,386 --> 00:48:54,751
Dad?

358
00:49:37,963 --> 00:49:43,367
Twinkle, twinkle, little star.

359
00:49:44,303 --> 00:49:49,570
How I wonder what you are.

360
00:50:53,506 --> 00:50:59,206
Twinkle, twinkle, little star.

361
00:51:00,312 --> 00:51:06,114
How I wonder what you are.

362
00:51:09,688 --> 00:51:14,086
I want to become Satoshi's little bride.

363
00:53:24,456 --> 00:53:28,092
Aqua plants shop, "Trash".

364
00:53:36,468 --> 00:53:40,402
Is this your shop?

365
00:53:43,008 --> 00:53:45,442
Are you the owner?

366
00:53:48,781 --> 00:53:50,671
Yes, I am.

367
00:54:00,693 --> 00:54:03,160
I met your father...

368
00:54:04,263 --> 00:54:06,663
...in my dream.

369
00:54:12,404 --> 00:54:14,895
Satoshi is waiting,

370
00:54:15,741 --> 00:54:18,500
so go back for him, he said.

371
00:54:19,478 --> 00:54:22,578
He told me how to get back.

372
00:54:29,521 --> 00:54:32,585
When I was about to leave, your father said...

373
00:54:35,327 --> 00:54:37,795
...he was happy,

374
00:54:44,636 --> 00:54:51,301
and that he loved you.

375
00:54:58,183 --> 00:55:08,210
"Karin, I'm sure you will see Satoshi again."

376
00:55:13,832 --> 00:55:17,299
"When you see him...

377
00:55:19,605 --> 00:55:23,768
...Say hello for me," he said.

378
00:56:18,063 --> 00:56:21,328
Welcome back, Karin.

379
00:56:26,104 --> 00:56:28,266
I'm back.

